phylo3D.parser.taxonomy
Class TaxonomyFileParser

java.lang.Object
  phylo3D.parser.taxonomy.TaxonomyFileParser
public class TaxonomyFileParser
extends java.lang.Object

Class provides functionality for parsing a taxonomy file. Each line in a taxonomy file is a taxonomic classification in tab dellimited format.

Author:
Tim Hughes (Computational Biology Unit - University of Bergen - Norway)

getStringsColourAssociations

public java.util.Vector getStringsColourAssociations(int matchingCol,
                                                     int colouringCol)
                                              throws InvalidInputsException
Produces a Vector of ObjectsColourAssociations where the objects are in order the matching column string (first object), the colouring column string (second object) and a string containing the full lineage (third object). The associated colour is not set

Parameters:
matchingCol - int denoting the column to be used as the matching column. First col is 1
colouringCol - int denoting the column to be used as the colouring column (it is strings in this column that can be associated with colours in the namesAndColours vector). First col is 1
Returns:
Vector of ObjectsColourAssociations
Throws:
InvalidInputsException
